title: Update the highest kafka offset metric correctly so that we can use it for alerting
body:
We currently have the capability to raise an alert if the metric kafka number of rows consumed goes to 0
in order to indicate a fault in the system that can cause us to stop consuming from Kafka.
However, this metric does not give the correct picture when there are no events in the kafka
pipeline, or when the kafka pipeline is burstly (e.g. pipelines from Samza jobs).

The idea here is to use the Kafka Highest Offset Consumed metric to detect these conditions.

In order for us to use this metric effectively, we need to make sure that this metric is set to 0
when we are not consuming any rows at all.

title: Pick the first server to report a row-limit reason as winner
body:
In LLC, if a server reaches row limit and stops consumption, we can make a reasonable assumption
that other servers will also reach row limit. If the first server (that starts the FSM) reports
a row-limit as reason for stopping, we pick that server as the winner and get the commit protocol
going right away.

We do not pay attention to the stop reason once we have picked a winner.

Added unit tests on controller and server side.

This change can be rolled out either controller first or server first. Until both are rolled out,
the optimization will not take effect.

Fixed a typo in PARTIAL_CONSUMING state name

title: Implement anomaly contribution to total metric and AnomalyDetectionInputContext
body:
By Q1 2017, we have on-board more than 20 metrics in ThirdEye. After monitoring performance for months, we discover clients care more about the anomaly's contribution to its total metric more than the severity it self. For example, an anomaly with 10% drop in US is more important than an anomaly with 90% drop in MX. We introduce an anomaly evaluation metric, Contribution to Total Metric (CTM), which evaluates the impact of the anomaly result to the total metric. 

1. Introduce anomaly contribution to total metric
2. Implement a centralized AnomalyDetectionInputContextBuilder to build up AnomalyDetectionInputContext
3. Users are able to enable the anomaly contribution in the setting of anomaly detection fucntion

title: Eliminate exception due to json parse error of table config zn record
body:
If a table config zn record fails to parse json, it is possible that controller fails to
take over leadership. We scan all table config records in PinotRealtimeSegmentManager.refreshWatchers()
method. One of the ZN records in the list will be null, and will throw an NPE as we iterate over
the list of tables. We do catch the exception, but then attempt to log the table name from
znRecord.getId(), and the log message throws an NPE

title: Implement lock-free thread safe on-heap mutable dictionaries

The dictionaries are thread safe under two conditions:
1. Single writer multiple readers
2. Reader always first get the dictId for a value, then use the dictId to fetch the value later
